---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Introduction">
  <div class="prose">
    <h1>Design System</h1>
    <p>
      A production-grade, token-driven design system for React. Built with the same
      infrastructure used by large product teams — typed tokens, accessible primitives,
      visual regression testing, and a living documentation site.
    </p>

    <h2>Quick start</h2>
    <pre><code>pnpm add @ds/tokens @ds/components</code></pre>
    <p>Then in your app's entry point:</p>
    <pre><code>{`import '@ds/tokens/css';     // design tokens as CSS variables
import '@ds/components/styles'; // component styles`}</code></pre>
    <p>Use components:</p>
    <pre><code>{`import { Button, Input, Heading, Text } from '@ds/components';

export function LoginForm() {
  return (
    <form>
      <Heading as="h1">Sign in</Heading>
      <Input label="Email" type="email" />
      <Button type="submit">Continue</Button>
    </form>
  );
}`}</code></pre>

    <h2>Architecture</h2>
    <p>
      The system is structured as a monorepo with three layers of packages, designed
      to be adopted incrementally:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>@ds/tokens</strong> — design tokens exported as CSS variables, TypeScript constants, and JSON</li>
      <li><strong>@ds/primitives</strong> — unstyled, accessible base components (Radix UI wrappers)</li>
      <li><strong>@ds/components</strong> — styled, token-driven components built on primitives</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Design principles</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Tokens first</strong> — every color, size, and spacing value lives in <code>tokens.json</code></li>
      <li><strong>Accessible by default</strong> — WCAG 2.1 AA, keyboard navigation, screen reader support</li>
      <li><strong>Typed throughout</strong> — TypeScript strict mode, no <code>any</code></li>
      <li><strong>Themeable</strong> — dark mode via CSS variable overrides</li>
      <li><strong>Tested</strong> — unit tests, a11y audits, and visual regression on every PR</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
